# Project Architecture & Context

Monorepo for VkSplat-based 3D Gaussian Splatting training research.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `ref/` | Frozen reference VkSplat (read-only ground truth; baseline tag `ref-baseline-2026-06-12`) |
| `ref/vksplat/` | Reference CMake/Python project root |
| `next/nlrc_vksplat/` | Clean-slate cross-platform rewrite (Phase 2 — all new work) |
| `test_data/` | Shared regression assets and golden masters (Phase 2) |
| `outputs/` | Training runs and buffer dumps (gitignored) |

## Targets

- **Windows x86_64** — MSVC or Clang via Ninja (`debug` / `release` presets in `ref/vksplat/CMakePresets.json`)
- **OpenHarmony ARM64** — OHOS NDK via Clang (`ohos-debug` / `ohos-release` presets)

## Compute stack

- Vulkan 1.2+
- Slang for core compute pipelines
- GLSL 460 for radix sort only (`glslc --target-env=vulkan1.2`)

## Class hierarchy (conceptual)

`VulkanGSPipeline` → `VulkanGSRenderer` → `VulkanGSTrainer`

## Config propagation

`vksplat_config.h` is the single source of truth for `VKSPLAT_*` constants. A generator emits `config_generated.slang`, `config_generated.glsl`, and `shader_config.json`. Host and shader profiles must stay in sync.

